{
  "texts": [
    "Our results demonstrate that queries constructed from frame elements consistently outperformed full-claim queries across both domains.",
    "This finding aligns with research by Madabushi (2024) showing that frame-semantics-based search strategies enhance retrieval effectiveness.",
    "The performance varied significantly between domains.",
    "For voting-related claims, even our bestperforming model (DistilBERT-TAS-B) achieved a modest recall@10 of 0.165, reflecting the complexity of bill matching.",
    "In contrast, OECD claim verification was easier for the model, with RoBERTa achieving a recall@5 of 0.726, likely due to the more constrained search space."
  ]
}